html:
Verb[edit]

iacēbitis

  1. second-person plural future active indicative of iaceō
    1. "you will lie prostrate, you will lie down; you will recline"
    2. "you will lie ill, you will be sick"
    3. "you will linger, you will tarry"
    4. "you will be placed or situated, you will lie"
    5. "you will be low, flat or level"
    6. "you will lie still"
    7. "you will lie dead"
    8. "you will lie in ruins"
    9. "you will hang down loose"
    10. (of the face or eyes) "you will be fixed on the ground, you will be cast down"
    11. "you will be indolent, idle or inactive"
    12. "you will lie dormant or abandoned, you will be of no avail"
    13. "you will lie overthrown; you will be refuted; you will be despised"
    14. (of speech or language) "you will be languid, dull or lifeless"
